{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_015JHktcdBy2uPVDz8P5FAgE","type":"tool_result","content":"366\t// MachineConfigPool describes a pool of MachineConfigs.\n367\t//\n368\t// Compatibility level 1: Stable within a major release for a minimum of 12 months or 3 minor releases (whichever is longer).\n369\t// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n370\t// +kubebuilder:resource:path=machineconfigpools,scope=Cluster,shortName=mcp\n371\t// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n372\t// +openshift:api-approved.openshift.io=https://github.com/openshift/api/pull/1453\n373\t// +openshift:file-pattern=cvoRunLevel=0000_80,operatorName=machine-config,operatorOrdering=01\n374\t// +kubebuilder:metadata:labels=\"openshift.io/operator-managed=\"\n375\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=Config,JSONPath=.status.configuration.name,type=string\n376\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=Updated,JSONPath=.status.conditions[?(@.type==\"Updated\")].status,type=string,description=When all the machines in the pool are updated to the correct machine config.\n377\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=Updating,JSONPath=.status.conditions[?(@.type==\"Updating\")].status,type=string,description=When at least one of machine is not either not updated or is in the process of updating to the desired machine config.\n378\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=Degraded,JSONPath=.status.conditions[?(@.type==\"Degraded\")].status,type=string,description=When progress is blocked on updating one or more nodes or the pool configuration is failing.\n379\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=MachineCount,JSONPath=.status.machineCount,type=number,description=Total number of machines in the machine config pool\n380\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=ReadyMachineCount,JSONPath=.status.readyMachineCount,type=number,description=Total number of ready machines targeted by the pool\n381\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=UpdatedMachineCount,JSONPath=.status.updatedMachineCount,type=number,description=Total number of machines targeted by the pool that have the CurrentMachineConfig as their config\n382\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=DegradedMachineCount,JSONPath=.status.degradedMachineCount,type=number,description=Total number of machines marked degraded (or unreconcilable)\n383\t// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=Age,JSONPath=.metadata.creationTimestamp,type=date\n384\t// +openshift:compatibility-gen:level=1\n385\ttype MachineConfigPool struct {\n386\t\tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n387\t\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n388\t\n389\t\t// spec contains the desired machine config pool configuration.\n390\t\t// +required\n391\t\tSpec MachineConfigPoolSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n392\t\n393\t\t// status contains observed information about the machine config pool.\n394\t\t// +optional\n395\t\tStatus MachineConfigPoolStatus `json:\"status\"`\n396\t}\n397\t\n398\t// MachineConfigPoolSpec is the spec for MachineConfigPool resource.\n399\ttype MachineConfigPoolSpec struct {\n400\t\t// machineConfigSelector specifies a label selector for MachineConfigs.\n401\t\t// Refer https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/labels/ on how label and selectors work.\n402\t\t// +optional\n403\t\tMachineConfigSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"machineConfigSelector,omitempty\"`\n404\t\n405\t\t// nodeSelector specifies a label selector for Machines\n406\t\t// +optional\n407\t\tNodeSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n408\t\n409\t\t// paused specifies whether or not changes to this machine config pool should be stopped.\n410\t\t// This includes generating new desiredMachineConfig and update of machines.\n411\t\t// +optional\n412\t\tPaused bool `json:\"paused\"`\n413\t\n414\t\t// maxUnavailable defines either an integer number or percentage\n415\t\t// of nodes in the pool that can go Unavailable during an update.\n416\t\t// This includes nodes Unavailable for any reason, including user\n417\t\t// initiated cordons, failing nodes, etc. The default value is 1.\n418\t\t//\n419\t\t// A value larger than 1 will mean multiple nodes going unavailable during\n420\t\t// the update, which may affect your workload stress on the remaining nodes.\n421\t\t// You cannot set this value to 0 to stop updates (it will default back to 1);\n422\t\t// to stop updates, use the 'paused' property instead. Drain will respect\n423\t\t// Pod Disruption Budgets (PDBs) such as etcd quorum guards, even if\n424\t\t// maxUnavailable is greater than one.\n425\t\t// +optional\n426\t\tMaxUnavailable *intstr.IntOrString `json:\"maxUnavailable,omitempty\"`\n427\t\n428\t\t// The targeted MachineConfig object for the machine config pool.\n429\t\t// +optional\n430\t\tConfiguration MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration `json:\"configuration\"`\n431\t\n432\t\t// pinnedImageSets specifies a sequence of PinnedImageSetRef objects for the\n433\t\t// pool. Nodes within this pool will preload and pin images defined in the\n434\t\t// PinnedImageSet. Before pulling images the MachineConfigDaemon will ensure\n435\t\t// the total uncompressed size of all the images does not exceed available\n436\t\t// resources. If the total size of the images exceeds the available\n437\t\t// resources the controller will report a Degraded status to the\n438\t\t// MachineConfigPool and not attempt to pull any images. Also to help ensure\n439\t\t// the kubelet can mitigate storage risk, the pinned_image configuration and\n440\t\t// subsequent service reload will happen only after all of the images have\n441\t\t// been pulled for each set. Images from multiple PinnedImageSets are loaded\n442\t\t// and pinned sequentially as listed. Duplicate and existing images will be\n443\t\t// skipped.\n444\t\t//\n445\t\t// Any failure to prefetch or pin images will result in a Degraded pool.\n446\t\t// Resolving these failures is the responsibility of the user. The admin\n447\t\t// should be proactive in ensuring adequate storage and proper image\n448\t\t// authentication exists in advance.\n449\t\t// +optional\n450\t\t// +listType=map\n451\t\t// +listMapKey=name\n452\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n453\t\tPinnedImageSets []PinnedImageSetRef `json:\"pinnedImageSets,omitempty\"`\n454\t\n455\t\t// osImageStream specifies an OS stream to be used for the pool.\n456\t\t//\n457\t\t// This field can be optionally set to a known OSImageStream name to change the\n458\t\t// OS and Extension images with a well-known, tested, release-provided set of images.\n459\t\t// This enables a streamlined way of switching the pool's node OS to a different version\n460\t\t// than the cluster default, such as transitioning to a major RHEL version.\n461\t\t//\n462\t\t// When set, the referenced stream overrides the cluster-wide OS\n463\t\t// images for the pool with the OS and Extensions associated to stream.\n464\t\t// When omitted, the pool uses the cluster-wide default OS images.\n465\t\t//\n466\t\t// +openshift:enable:FeatureGate=OSStreams\n467\t\t// +optional\n468\t\tOSImageStream OSImageStreamReference `json:\"osImageStream,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n469\t}\n470\t\n471\ttype OSImageStreamReference struct {\n472\t\t// name is a required reference to an OSImageStream to be used for the pool.\n473\t\t//\n474\t\t// It must be a valid RFC 1123 subdomain between 1 and 253 characters in length,\n475\t\t// consisting of lowercase alphanumeric characters, hyphens ('-'), and periods ('.').\n476\t\t//\n477\t\t// +required\n478\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n479\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength=253\n480\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"!format.dns1123Subdomain().validate(self).hasValue()\",message=\"a RFC 1123 subdomain must consist of lower case alphanumeric characters, '-' or '.', and must start and end with an alphanumeric character.\"\n481\t\tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n482\t}\n483\t\n484\ttype PinnedImageSetRef struct {\n485\t\t// name is a reference to the name of a PinnedImageSet.  Must adhere to\n486\t\t// RFC-1123 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1123).\n487\t\t// Made up of one of more period-separated (.) segments, where each segment\n488\t\t// consists of alphanumeric characters and hyphens (-), must begin and end\n489\t\t// with an alphanumeric character, and is at most 63 characters in length.\n490\t\t// The total length of the name must not exceed 253 characters.\n491\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n492\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength=253\n493\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern=`^([a-zA-Z0-9]|[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9\\-]{0,61}[a-zA-Z0-9])(\\.([a-zA-Z0-9]|[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9\\-]{0,61}[a-zA-Z0-9]))*$`\n494\t\t// +required\n495\t\tName string `json:\"name\"`\n496\t}\n497\t\n498\t// MachineConfigPoolStatus is the status for MachineConfigPool resource.\n499\ttype MachineConfigPoolStatus struct {\n500\t\t// observedGeneration represents the generation observed by the controller.\n501\t\t// +optional\n502\t\tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n503\t\n504\t\t// configuration represents the current MachineConfig object for the machine config pool.\n505\t\t// +optional\n506\t\tConfiguration MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration `json:\"configuration\"`\n507\t\n508\t\t// machineCount represents the total number of machines in the machine config pool.\n509\t\t// +optional\n510\t\tMachineCount int32 `json:\"machineCount\"`\n511\t\n512\t\t// updatedMachineCount represents the total number of machines targeted by the pool that have the CurrentMachineConfig as their config.\n513\t\t// +optional\n514\t\tUpdatedMachineCount int32 `json:\"updatedMachineCount\"`\n515\t\n516\t\t// readyMachineCount represents the total number of ready machines targeted by the pool.\n517\t\t// +optional\n518\t\tReadyMachineCount int32 `json:\"readyMachineCount\"`\n519\t\n520\t\t// unavailableMachineCount represents the total number of unavailable (non-ready) machines targeted by the pool.\n521\t\t// A node is marked unavailable if it is in updating state or NodeReady condition is false.\n522\t\t// +optional\n523\t\tUnavailableMachineCount int32 `json:\"unavailableMachineCount\"`\n524\t\n525\t\t// degradedMachineCount represents the total number of machines marked degraded (or unreconcilable)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01VmBJvAx2oNMkFPuwULsyHB","session_id":"2fe54bd0-271e-4b69-992f-525b199bb078","uuid":"dcf2de28-9a9b-4a90-9cdb-8999f0fadd32","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:22:08.908Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfigPool selector examples and logic"}
