{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01VmBJvAx2oNMkFPuwULsyHB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a complete summary of findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfigPool YAML Examples\n\n**Built-in pools (manifests/ — production manifests)**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/master.machineconfigpool.yaml`\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: master\n  labels:\n    \"operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/required-for-upgrade\": \"\"\n    \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/mco-built-in\": \"\"\n    \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/master\": \"\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\": \"master\"\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/master: \"\"\n```\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` — identical pattern with `worker` role.\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/arbiter.machineconfigpool.yaml` — arbiter role, also has `required-for-upgrade` label.\n\n**Simple examples (examples/)**\n\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/etcd.machineconfigpool.yaml` — etcd pool with `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: etcd`.\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/machineconfigpool.crd.yaml` — the CRD manifest itself.\n\n**Test server fixture**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-pools/test-pool.yaml` — shows full spec + status scaffold including `configuration.name`, `maxUnavailable: null`, `paused: false`, and all status count fields.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How machineConfigSelector Is Processed\n\nThe selector is used in two key places in the render controller:\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/render/render_controller.go`\n\n**Sync path (line ~510-535):** During each reconcile cycle:\n```go\neverything := metav1.LabelSelector{}\nif reflect.DeepEqual(pool.Spec.MachineConfigSelector, &everything) {\n    ctrl.eventRecorder.Eventf(pool, corev1.EventTypeWarning, \"SelectingAll\", ...)\n    return nil\n}\nselector, err := metav1.LabelSelectorAsSelector(pool.Spec.MachineConfigSelector)\nmcs, err := ctrl.mcLister.List(selector)\n```\nAn empty/nil selector is rejected (emits a warning event and bails). Otherwise it converts the `LabelSelector` struct into a Go `labels.Selector` and lists all `MachineConfig` objects from the cache that match. The matched MachineConfigs are then sorted by name and merged into a rendered config.\n\n**Bootstrap path (line ~959-979, `getMachineConfigsForPool`):** Same logic — convert to selector, skip if empty, then filter a static list of configs.\n\n**Pool-to-config reverse lookup (line ~374-393):** Also done in reverse — finding which pools a given `MachineConfig` belongs to, by iterating all pools and testing if their selector matches the MC's labels. An empty selector matches nothing (not everything).\n\n**Key rule enforced:** A nil or empty `LabelSelector{}` is treated as \"select nothing\" — not as the Kubernetes default of \"select everything\". This is an intentional safety guard.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Infra / Custom Pool Examples\n\n**Custom pool template (the canonical pattern for user-created pools):**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool.yaml`\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - { key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [ worker, \"${NAME}\" ] }\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/${NAME}: \"\"\n```\nNote the `matchExpressions` with `In: [worker, <custom-role>]` — this is the standard pattern for custom pools that inherit from worker.\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool-osimagestream.yaml` — extends the above with an `osImageStream.name` field.\n\n**Infra selector** (used in test helpers, `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/helpers/helpers.go`):\n```go\nInfraSelector = metav1.AddLabelToSelector(&metav1.LabelSelector{}, \"node-role/infra\", \"\")\n```\nThere is no production YAML for an \"infra\" pool, only this test helper selector.\n\n**layered-worker** (bootstrap test fixture):\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` — a custom pool with its own distinct role label (not inheriting worker), used for image-layering tests.\n\n---\n\n## 4. MachineConfigPool Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go` (lines 385-469)\n\n`MachineConfigPoolSpec` fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects MachineConfig objects to include. Supports both `matchLabels` and `matchExpressions`. |\n| `nodeSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects nodes belonging to this pool. |\n| `paused` | `bool` | Stops rendering and node updates when true. |\n| `maxUnavailable` | `*intstr.IntOrString` | Integer or percentage; default 1. Cannot be 0 — use `paused` instead. |\n| `configuration` | `MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration` | Reference to the current rendered MachineConfig for the pool. |\n| `pinnedImageSets` | `[]PinnedImageSetRef` | Up to 100 named PinnedImageSets to preload on nodes. |\n| `osImageStream` | `OSImageStreamReference` | Feature-gated (`OSStreams`). Overrides OS image for the pool with a named stream (e.g., `rhel-9`). |\n\n**ValidatingAdmissionPolicy enforcement** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/machineconfigcontroller/custom-machine-config-pool-selector-validatingadmissionpolicy.yaml`): Custom pools (non-master/worker/arbiter) must use `matchExpressions` with `In: [worker, ...]` or `NotIn: [worker, ...]`. All custom pools must inherit from the worker pool — a `matchLabels: role: my-custom-role` alone would be rejected by this policy."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fe54bd0-271e-4b69-992f-525b199bb078","uuid":"c3cf093d-d89e-4c3b-a0d4-2f7331da4f97","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:22:56.333Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator, find:\n1. Example MachineConfigPool YAML/JSON definitions (look in docs/, manifests/, test fixtures, or examples directories)\n2. How machineConfigSelector works in the codebase — look for where it's processed or validated\n3. Any infra or custom pool examples\n4. The MachineConfigPool CRD or type definition to understand available fields\n\nSearch breadth: medium. Focus on real YAML examples and the type struct definition.","agentId":"a12d71965a7d591c1","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\nHere is a complete summary of findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. MachineConfigPool YAML Examples\n\n**Built-in pools (manifests/ — production manifests)**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/master.machineconfigpool.yaml`\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: master\n  labels:\n    \"operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/required-for-upgrade\": \"\"\n    \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/mco-built-in\": \"\"\n    \"pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/master\": \"\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      \"machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\": \"master\"\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/master: \"\"\n```\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` — identical pattern with `worker` role.\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/arbiter.machineconfigpool.yaml` — arbiter role, also has `required-for-upgrade` label.\n\n**Simple examples (examples/)**\n\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/etcd.machineconfigpool.yaml` — etcd pool with `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: etcd`.\n- `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/examples/machineconfigpool.crd.yaml` — the CRD manifest itself.\n\n**Test server fixture**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/server/testdata/machine-pools/test-pool.yaml` — shows full spec + status scaffold including `configuration.name`, `maxUnavailable: null`, `paused: false`, and all status count fields.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How machineConfigSelector Is Processed\n\nThe selector is used in two key places in the render controller:\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/render/render_controller.go`\n\n**Sync path (line ~510-535):** During each reconcile cycle:\n```go\neverything := metav1.LabelSelector{}\nif reflect.DeepEqual(pool.Spec.MachineConfigSelector, &everything) {\n    ctrl.eventRecorder.Eventf(pool, corev1.EventTypeWarning, \"SelectingAll\", ...)\n    return nil\n}\nselector, err := metav1.LabelSelectorAsSelector(pool.Spec.MachineConfigSelector)\nmcs, err := ctrl.mcLister.List(selector)\n```\nAn empty/nil selector is rejected (emits a warning event and bails). Otherwise it converts the `LabelSelector` struct into a Go `labels.Selector` and lists all `MachineConfig` objects from the cache that match. The matched MachineConfigs are then sorted by name and merged into a rendered config.\n\n**Bootstrap path (line ~959-979, `getMachineConfigsForPool`):** Same logic — convert to selector, skip if empty, then filter a static list of configs.\n\n**Pool-to-config reverse lookup (line ~374-393):** Also done in reverse — finding which pools a given `MachineConfig` belongs to, by iterating all pools and testing if their selector matches the MC's labels. An empty selector matches nothing (not everything).\n\n**Key rule enforced:** A nil or empty `LabelSelector{}` is treated as \"select nothing\" — not as the Kubernetes default of \"select everything\". This is an intentional safety guard.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Infra / Custom Pool Examples\n\n**Custom pool template (the canonical pattern for user-created pools):**\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool.yaml`\n```yaml\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - { key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role, operator: In, values: [ worker, \"${NAME}\" ] }\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/${NAME}: \"\"\n```\nNote the `matchExpressions` with `In: [worker, <custom-role>]` — this is the standard pattern for custom pools that inherit from worker.\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/custom-machine-config-pool-osimagestream.yaml` — extends the above with an `osImageStream.name` field.\n\n**Infra selector** (used in test helpers, `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/helpers/helpers.go`):\n```go\nInfraSelector = metav1.AddLabelToSelector(&metav1.LabelSelector{}, \"node-role/infra\", \"\")\n```\nThere is no production YAML for an \"infra\" pool, only this test helper selector.\n\n**layered-worker** (bootstrap test fixture):\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineconfigpool.yaml` — a custom pool with its own distinct role label (not inheriting worker), used for image-layering tests.\n\n---\n\n## 4. MachineConfigPool Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types.go` (lines 385-469)\n\n`MachineConfigPoolSpec` fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects MachineConfig objects to include. Supports both `matchLabels` and `matchExpressions`. |\n| `nodeSelector` | `*metav1.LabelSelector` | Selects nodes belonging to this pool. |\n| `paused` | `bool` | Stops rendering and node updates when true. |\n| `maxUnavailable` | `*intstr.IntOrString` | Integer or percentage; default 1. Cannot be 0 — use `paused` instead. |\n| `configuration` | `MachineConfigPoolStatusConfiguration` | Reference to the current rendered MachineConfig for the pool. |\n| `pinnedImageSets` | `[]PinnedImageSetRef` | Up to 100 named PinnedImageSets to preload on nodes. |\n| `osImageStream` | `OSImageStreamReference` | Feature-gated (`OSStreams`). Overrides OS image for the pool with a named stream (e.g., `rhel-9`). |\n\n**ValidatingAdmissionPolicy enforcement** (`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/manifests/machineconfigcontroller/custom-machine-config-pool-selector-validatingadmissionpolicy.yaml`): Custom pools (non-master/worker/arbiter) must use `matchExpressions` with `In: [worker, ...]` or `NotIn: [worker, ...]`. All custom pools must inherit from the worker pool — a `matchLabels: role: my-custom-role` alone would be rejected by this policy."}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":76969,"totalTokens":37033,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1894,"cache_read_input_tokens":33229,"output_tokens":1909,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1894},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":20,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":7,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
