: worker`) are **also picked up** \u2014 that's the mandatory inheritance. Your infra configs layer on top of the worker base.\n\n---\n\n## Why MCO Requires This\n\nThe render controller (`pkg/controller/render/render_controller.go`) merges all matched MachineConfigs by name order. Without the worker base, infra nodes would lack the OS configuration that MCO relies on (Ignition base, CRI-O, kubelet, etc.). Allowing a fully isolated pool would produce nodes that diverge from a known-good base in ways MCO can't safely manage.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** a completely worker-independent selector is not achievable in stock MCO \u2014 the VAP actively rejects it on every API call. Use `In: [worker, infra]` and use the `infra` role label exclusively on your infra-specific configs to keep your customizations cleanly separated from the worker baseline.", "stop_reason": "end_turn", "session_id": "2fe54bd0-271e-4b69-992f-525b199bb078", "total_cost_usd": 0.31272089999999997, "usage": {"input_tokens": 7, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 6005, "cache_read_input_tokens": 101135, "output_tokens": 2279, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 6005}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-sonnet-4-6": {"inputTokens": 446, "outputTokens": 7027, "cacheReadInputTokens": 333518, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 28246, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.31272089999999997, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 32000}}, "permission_denials": [], "terminal_reason": "completed", "fast_mode_state": "off", "uuid": "65e6eba3-57e7-47f4-b42a-25eec2378eea", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:23:31.081Z"}